  "texts": [
    "Lastly, the downstream LFSurv section of AUTOSurv is a Cox Proportional Hazard network, and studies have tried to overcome the proportional hazard constraint to yield more realistic predictions 12, 14, 48.",
    "We could also adjust the learning objectives of AUTOSurv accordingly to model time-varying effects of the input features and/or to learn patient-specific survival distributions 14, 48.",
    "Surv is a deep learning model for cancer prognosis prediction combining multi-omics and demographic/clinical data.",
    "There are three major parts to our framework: (1) pathway information incorporated multi-omics variational autoencoder (VAE) with KL-annealing learning strategy 49 (KL-PMVAE) for efficient multi-omics integration and latent-feature extraction; (2) latent-feature-fed survival network (LFSurv) integrates latent features extracted by the VAE model with demographic/clinical variables and conducts final prognosis prediction; and (3) DeepSHAP 25, 26 interpretation approach applied to the trained AUTOSurv model (KL-PMVAE plus LFSurv) assigns importance scores to input features and identifies the features that make important contribution in distinguishing between the high-and low-risk patients.",
    "The workflow of AUTOSurv is illustrated in Fig. 1."
